    "proposed an admittance controller by varying the damping according to the approximation of human arm stiffness.",
    "Moreover, a similar approach by varying the robot's damping according to the human arm stiffness, at a low velocity, was also developed [19].",
    "Yang et al.,in [20] proposed a robot controller that reproduced how humans adapt to interaction forces and instability.",
    "The robot controller learned to adjust to unaccounted deviations using feedback and feedforward parameters and minimized the motion errors achieving a variable impedance behavior.",
